						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That's the best thing about emulation, the crisp, crystal clear, unedited, unstretched perfect 256x240 image you get.</div>
<br />Except the graphics in NES and Super NES games weren't drawn for unstretched. They were drawn for the 8:7 stretch ratio that the NES PPU spits out. You can see this in <em>Dr. Mario</em>: if you play unstretched, the magnifying glass in the lower left corner is not circular.</div>

